<DocsPageTitle Path="Start">
    Blazorise Templates Guide
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    The Blazorise Templates allows you to quickly setup a Blazor project of your choice (Server or WebAssembly),
    with any of our Providers, and with a default starting look.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    The Blazorise Templates are based on the <Anchor To="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/tools/dotnet-new" Target="Target.Blank">dotnet templates</Anchor> feature.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Step 1: Download & Install Blazorise.Templates
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader>
        You do so by using the CLI <Anchor To="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/tools/dotnet-new-install" Target="Target.Blank">dotnet new install</Anchor> feature.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="TemplatesInstallExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Versioning">
        We use our Templates versioning to match & install the latest corresponding Blazorise major & minor version.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        For example:
        <UnorderedList>
            <UnorderedListItem>
                Blazorise.Templates::1.1.* will always try to install the latest 1.1 Blazorise
            </UnorderedListItem>
            <UnorderedListItem>
                Blazorise.Templates::1.2.* will always try to install the latest 1.2 Blazorise
            </UnorderedListItem>
        </UnorderedList>
        If you want to install a specific version do some by passing in the version.
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="TemplatesVersionInstallExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Step 2: With Blazorise.Templates installed you may now use the CLI or the Visual Studio IDE to create your new Blazorise solution!
</DocsPageSubtitle>

